---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Moving around during the Monaco Grand Prix | Guide";
const description = "English guide to plan your trips to and from Monaco during the Grand Prix: transfers, traffic and timing.";
const canonical = "/en/guide-monaco-grand-prix-transport.html";
---

<BaseLayout 
  title={title}
  description={description}
  currentPage="guide-monaco-grand-prix-transport"
  canonical={canonical}
>

    <nav class="breadcrumbs container" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/en/">Home</a> › <a href="/en/guides">VTC Guides</a> › <span>Monaco Grand Prix transport</span>
    </nav>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">Events guide</div>
          <h1 class="section-title">Moving around during the Monaco Grand Prix</h1>
          <p>On race days, access to Monaco is very controlled and traffic can be heavy. A bit of preparation will make your experience much smoother.</p>
        </div>

        <section class="section" style="padding-top:1.5rem">
          <h2>Think in terms of time, not only distance</h2>
          <p>The distance between Nice and Monaco is short, but driving time can vary a lot. Always allow generous margins, especially before sessions or hospitality events.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" style="padding-top:1.5rem">
          <h2>Using a private driver for race days</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Arrange transfers to and from your hotel, villa or yacht.</li>
            <li>Share your ticket zone or hospitality location so your driver can plan drop-off and pick-up points.</li>
            <li>Book late returns in advance to avoid last-minute stress.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" style="padding-top:1.5rem">
          <h2>Sending a clear request</h2>
          <p>When you send a request through the <a href="/reservation">booking form</a>, mention the days you will attend the Grand Prix, the number of guests and your accommodation area. This will help design a realistic transport plan.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>
  
</BaseLayout>
